<subSubSection pageId="158" pageNumber="159" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="158.[151,1436,1691,2026]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis box="[151,233,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Leaves</emphasis>
veins raised and rectangular in cross-section adaxially; basal pinna 1.3(0.6–2.0) cm wide; apical pinna 7.3(2.7–11.3) cm wide. 
<emphasis box="[443,617,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Inflorescences</emphasis>
prophyll margins with irregular, spine-like projections; flower pits usually spirally arranged, distantly spaced.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
