<subSubSection pageId="158" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="158.[151,1436,1691,2026]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,505,1884,1910]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
There is geographic discontinuity, and specimens come from three different mountain areas. Specimens from the Cordilleras Cutucú and Cóndor have more pinnae per side of the rachis than those from the eastern slopes of the main Cordillera. However, there are too few specimens to test for differences. Jean-Christophe Pintaud (pers. comm.) reports that this subspecies also occurs in adjacent 
<collectingCountry box="[1356,1414,2000,2026]" name="Peru" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
